issue.title: Sideframe History Nav Buttons Wrap
issue.body:
## Description

The "CMS Sideframe History" navigation's triangles are wrapping. Tested on three browsers.

## Steps to reproduce

0. Be logged in to your CMS website.
1. Open your CMS website homepage.
2. In top CMS admin nav bar, click on (Site Name) > "Administration…"
3. Look at the top-right of the sidebar that takes up most of the screen.

## Expected behaviour

The triangle nav buttons (◀▶) are on one line.

## Actual behaviour

The triangle nav buttons (◀▶) are on two lines.

## Screenshots

| Browser | Problem | Fix (1 pixel) |
| - | - | - |
| Chromium-based | ![brave - sidebar history nav buttons wrap - 65px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/04c0d47b-d315-4a9c-9c6c-0e18e2653a3f) | ![brave - sidebar history nav buttons fit - 66px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/dbe58616-1fb6-46fd-b34f-910bb81341d4) |
| Firefox | ![firefox - sidebar history nav buttons wrap - 65px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/e987c003-db21-4bdc-9666-b2fa08057944) | ![firefox - sidebar history nav buttons fit - 66px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/4ca985a4-a633-4cb2-8b34-5843ad0ad0e4) |
| Safari | ![safari - sidebar history nav buttons wrap - 65px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/a5050d0e-b3d6-4b59-8647-89e15b7abd3f) | ![safari - sidebar history nav buttons fit - 66px](https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/assets/62723358/77a8f19e-ea02-461a-8630-f47b45413b89) |


## Additional information (CMS/Python/Django versions)

Django CMS: 3.11.4
Django: 4.2
Python: 3

## Do you want to help fix this issue?

* [x] Yes, I want to help fix this issue and I will join #workgroup-pr-review on [Slack](https://www.django-cms.org/slack) to confirm with the community that a PR is welcome. 
* No, I only want to report the issue.

> **Note**
> Culprit code seems to be 
https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/blob/3.11.4/cms/static/cms/sass/components/_sideframe.scss#L99-L100.

pull_request.title: fix: `.load` jQuery method erroneously replaced by `.on('load')`
pull_request.body:
## Description

* Fixes #7677.
   jQuery before version 3 had two `.load` methods, one of which was removed in jQuery 3 and    replaced by `.on('load', ...)`. The change form needs to use the other `.load` method, which    creates an Ajax request and inserts the target into the result.
   Change in `cms/js/modules/cms.changeform.js`:
   https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/blob/ed21f1a7808482d67ce3ea1752d54c114bfeb1ab/cms/static/cms/js/modules/cms.changeform.js#L14

* Ports forward #6457 
    https://github.com/django-cms/django-cms/blob/04353efc7ff41100f11aee13a1f0d9a4df84610f/cms/templatetags/cms_admin.py#L219-L225

* Cherry-picks related #7635 which was incorrectly merged into `release/4.1.x`
   (all other changes)


## Related resources

<!--
Add here links to existing issues or conversation from GitHub
or any other resource.
-->

* #7677 
* https://api.jquery.com/load/
* #7635

pull_request.title: fix: Update transifex pull strings script for v3 in alignment with v4
pull_request.body:
## Description

The v3 transifex pull script contains a bug which reverts all results from `./manage.py compilemessages` during the built of a new v3 version.

This has been fixed in the v4 repo when building django CMS v4 release candidates. It is important to fix this for v3, too, since typos in some translations have been detected.

The solution is to **first** undo any changes to the `.po` files which are trivial (date stamps only, e.g.) and **then** run `compilemessages`.
